<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><i>Dis is Numbuk's first attempt at writing epic story.  It especially Numbuk's first attempt at writing story from an ogre perspective.  Me will <b>try</b> to update dis tory every day or so, so keep checking back.<br />
<br />
Please no reply to dis thread, so it make it easier to read from chapter to chapter.  If yous have any comments, suggestions, or anyting about dis story, please post it in <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=850" target="_blank">Dis Thread</a>.<br />
<br />
Me hope yous enjoy dis story as much as me is writing it.<br />
<br />
Oh, and me never really been writer before, so grammar stink.  But hey, me is an ogre, so cut some slack!</i><br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Chapter 1.</b><br />
<br />
<br />
In a small cave in Oggok dere lived a nice ogre family.  Like many ogre families, dey had a mommy, a daddy, and two boy ogres.  Dis family was da Emgood family and dey were a happy bunch.  Smash was da older brudder and he would play "How Many Lumps Can I Make Yous  Head Get" with younger brother Bash.<br />
<br />
Dis was a happy time.  Daddy Emgood would fish all day long and sell his wares to the shopkeepers.  Mommy Emgood would spend her days dirtying up da unsightly "clean spots" in da cave and make her usual Froglok Booger Pie.  All was going berry well, until one night.<br />
<br />
"How was yous day, Bash?" asked Daddy Emgood while his family was sitting at da dinner table.<br />
<br />
"It fun!" said Bash excitedly.  "Smash gave me record number of lumps on head!  He gave me 14!  At least, dat what he say.  But me tink he no can count good."<br />
<br />
"Shut up," growled Smash, "Yous is just a dumbhead!  Me give yous more tomorrow!"<br />
<br />
"Now be quiet both of yous," barked Mommy Emgood.  "Don't make me have to give you both baths!"<br />
<br />
Both young ogres immediately slammed deir mouths shut and began eating quietly.  Nothing was heard but da sound of chomping and slurping.  Nothing, until da cave door exploded into a pile of smoldering rubble.<br />
<br />
Da Emgood family looked up with a shock.  Standing at da door was a mean looking goblin wizard.  Hand still smoking from some spell, he point a finger at Daddy Emgood.<br />
<br />
"Ah ha!  So you're the one I've been hunting for all these years!" da goblin cackled gleefully.  "Now I've found you, and now you shall die!"<br />
<br />
Without another word, da wizard send two fireballs hurling into da Emgood family.  It hit both Mommy and Daddy Emgood and dey disappear into a cloud of smoke and ash.  Bash and Smash just look on in disbelief and horror.  The goblin just smiles and blows on his finger.<br />
<br />
"That takes care of that," da goblin say. "No more worrying about that ogre coming to slay me."<br />
<br />
"Yous dumbhead," Bash yell out sobbing.  "He was good ogre!  He no wanted to kill anyone but gnomes, frogloks, orcs, bears, lizards, giants, treants, mammoths, sarnaks, skeletons, zombies, beetles, griffins, and dorfs.  He no wanted to kill goblin magic ting!"<br />
<br />
"Ah, but he would have," said the goblin.  "He was prophecied to kill me, so I just did the deed first.  Prophecy speaks of an ogre who will be my downfall, and I have tracked him to this house.  And by process of elimination, I figured it was your dad since you two are both too small and your mother was just a female.  So you see, now I can be safe."<br />
<br />
"Me tink yous is telling us too much information," said Smash.  "But why did yous kills our mudder too?"  Smash's eyes started to well up in tears.<br />
<br />
"I've nothing to fear from telling you too much information," remarked da goblin snidely.  "You're just kids!  As for your mother, well, I just happened to miss with my first fireball and hitting her was an accident.  Oh well, nobody's perfect."<br />
<br />
"Yous name is... Smellybreath?  Or is dat just a trait?" asked Bash inquisitively.<br />
<br />
"It is both a name and a trait.  How did you know it was my name?"<br />
<br />
"Yous have a sticker on chest dat say, 'Hello!  My name is Smellybreath' with words 'A.A. Meeting' at bottom."<br />
<br />
"Oh.  Right.  I forgot to take that off."<br />
<br />
"Ok den.  We will not forget.  Us is gonna train now for few years and we'll bash yous good!"<br />
<br />
"Good luck with that."  Smellybreath chuckled to himself.  "I'd like to see <b>that</b> happen.  Yeah right!  Take care, you little kids!  I am sure I'll never be seeing you ever again!"<br />
<br />
And with dat, da goblin vanished in a puff of smoke.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
