	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Bash and Smash never forgot da face of mean goblin who killed deir parents.  Dey never forgot da evil glint in his red eyes, but mostly, dey never forgot his horrible breath.  Dere was a good reason his name was Smellybreath.<br />
<br />
Dey both went and lived with deir ogre grandfather.  Deir granddad was an ogre hippy, so he would always be using "special herbs" and listening to ogre sitar music.  <br />
<br />
Bash and Smash no had need of such tings, and so began to teach demselves da art of combat.  Dey knew dere was more to it dan just picking up big stick and smashing tings wit it, and dey knew it gonna take more dan said stick to bash Smellybreath.  Dey practiced hours on end learning different moves, different swings, even a few shamanistic spells.  Dey did nothing else but practice fighting wit each other.<br />
<br />
Well, until a few years later when dey discovered ogre girls... but let's skip past dat part right now.  Fast forward a few years and us is now on same page.<br />
<br />
"Moondoggy," said Papa Smurpheater while sitting in a meditative pose in da living room, "come on in here child."<br />
<br />
"Grandpa, my name is Bash," Bash said getting tired of reminding his grandfather of what his real name is.  "Me hate name Moondoggy!"<br />
<br />
"Right, right.  Far out, man!  Moondoggy, can you go grab your brother Shroombaby?"<br />
<br />
"Grandpa," said Smash, "Me name no is Shroombaby and me is already here!"<br />
<br />
"Right, right.  Outta Sight!  Feel the love.  The love!  Then cherish the colors.  The colors!"<br />
<br />
Bash and Smash looked at each other and rolled deir eyes.  Dey had been through dis routine before.  Once grandpa got going, he never came back until a few hours later.  Luckily, dis time, he snapped out of it.<br />
<br />
"Whoa!  Trippy.  Now look here, flower children, I have had a revelation this night."<br />
<br />
"Like when you had a revelation dat we should spend adolescence naked wit our names painted on our butts?" Bash asked not all too kindly.<br />
<br />
"Yeah, dat was embarrassing!" excalimed Smash.  "Us still get picked on today!  How about da time yous had a revelation dat lizardmen now like ogres and we should go try and make friends wit dem?"<br />
<br />
"Me still have lizard teeth stuck in me arm!" shouted Bash.<br />
<br />
"Settle down, lovemonkeys," Papa said calmly.  "This hip revelation came from the Sacred Peyote."<br />
<br />
Both brothers just stared in silence.  Papa's revelations were never wrong when he smoked the Sacred Peyote.  It was rumored he had pilfered it from a wizard's spire long ago in his adventuring days.  He rarely touched it, but when he did, his predictions always came true.  Well. most of da time.<br />
<br />
"Now, you should know that one of you isn't going to like this," Papa said with glazed eyes.  "I have had a vision of that goblin you crazy cats always are talking about.  I have had a vision of where he's hiding out, and what you boys are to do about it."<br />
<br />
Both ogres just stared with jaws agape.  Dis was good news.  Dey would do anyting to smash dat dumbhead goblin.  Dey waited intently for da old ogre to continue.<br />
<br />
"It appears," Papa began, "that unrighteous oppressor has been shacking up in a mountain range known as Trakanon's Teeth.  And, my vision has said that only one of you may go to slay him and the other must stay behind.  If it is any other way, then you will both be killed.  Whoever leaves, man, it must be tonight.  And, man, if you don't do the deed within three months, it'll be too late."<br />
<br />
"What do yous mean, 'too late'?" asked Bash.<br />
<br />
"I'm not sure, Moondoggy.  It just says, 'too late.'"<br />
<br />
"It actually say, <i>'too late,'</i>?" Smash interjected.<br />
<br />
"Well, no.  I saw the vision of a donkey skinnydipping in a vat of chocolate ice cream.  We ogre hippies concluded long ago that <i>that</i> particular image means 'too late.'"<br />
<br />
Da young ogres could no deny da wisdom of da ogre hippies of yore.  Dey thought about what deir grandpa had told dem.  Dey thought so hard it make deir heads hurt.  Finally, Smash stood up.<br />
<br />
"Me will go!  Me will go smash goblin!  Me is oldest, and derefore me should be one who goes!"<br />
<br />
Bash didn't like da idea of his brudder on his own and felt confident dat he himself could kill mean old Smellybreath.  But, he and his brother have become almost perfect equals in fighting over the past few years.  He no could argue with his older brudder, and he knew no udder ogre -- udder dan himself -- was suited for da job.<br />
<br />
"Smash," Bash said with tears in eyes, "Me know yous will avenge our parent's death.  Me sure you not gonna fail and den force me to go on adventure of me own.  Make sure yous give dat wizard an extra good bash for me."<br />
<br />
"Me will.  Me promise.  Me will come back and den us will finally be like regular ogres."<br />
<br />
"Shroombaby," Papa said placing his arms on Smash's shoulders, "Take care of yourself.  I have put together a journey pack for you.  It has all the things you will ever need.  Well, it has all the things <b>I</b> ever needed on adventures.  Hurry up and take it and get out of here!"<br />
<br />
With a nod, Smash picked up da ogre backpack off of da floor.  He gave his family each a good, big ogre hug and den opened up da door.  He stepped out into a starlit sky, and jogged off towards the city gates.<br />
<br />
"Me hope he be ok," sniffled Bash.<br />
<br />
"Shroombaby's got a good head on his shoulders.  Nothing's gonna happen to him.  He'll be back before the three months are up.  Man, I've got 'the munchies' something fierce!"<br />
<br />
A year passed by and dey never heard from Smash.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
