<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Lilting was a young male halfling who grew up in Rivervale with his family.  Like almost all halflings, Lilting was a druid.  His mother was a druid, his father was a druid, and his uncle was a used armor salesman... but we won't speak of dat black sheep of the family.<br />
<br />
On a particularly hot afternoon, Lilting was on da outskirts of town trying various techniques of da druid ways.  Da blond haired halfling liked to try unconventional methods of his magic.  He thought dere was more to being a druid dan what most people tink.  Unfortunately, he just wasn't very good at spell casting at all.  And even more unfortunately, he was a bit clumsy and some would also say a little slow in da head.<br />
<br />
"See that bixie over there?" Lilting asked his halfling buddy who was out wit him dis day.<br />
<br />
"Of course I do," his friend Nappyhair replied wit a hint of irritation.  "It's five feet in front of us!"<br />
<br />
"Well watch this!  Watch how a tried and true method can be used more effectively when reversed!"<br />
<br />
"Whatever," Nappyhair responded not really, caring anymore.<br />
<br />
Lilting began waving his arms around and chanting.  Blue sparks emanating from his fingers, he spoke da magic words. "I call upon the spirits of wolf!  Come to me and enter this bixie!"<br />
<br />
Nappyhair, hardly listening but catching dat last line, snapped his head in Lilting's direction wit pure puzzlement.  <br />
<br />
"Are you sure that you want to do..."<br />
<br />
"Shhh!  Watch!  Trust me," the halfling said as he quickly began casting his second spell.  "Sticky feet come to me, Ensnare my foe and don't let him free!"<br />
<br />
Instead of pointing at da bixie, however, Lilting pointed to himself.  His feet seemed to magically acquire some powerful adhesive dat made it much harder for him to run.<br />
<br />
"Ummm..." is all Nappyhair could say.  He was in complete bewilderment.<br />
<br />
"I call this a 'Reverse Kite.'" Lilting said proudly.  "You see, I figure that if most druids have a hard time when they are sped up and monsters are slowed down, that if the opposite were applied then I should have an easier time with everything.  The theory is sound!"<br />
<br />
"Ummm..." is all Nappyhair could say as he looked at his friend in disbelief.  About dis time, da small bee-like fairy realized what was going on.  It turned and made a mad dash for Lilting.<br />
<br />
"Run!" yelped Nappyhair.  "You've made it mad!"<br />
<br />
"Like I said, don't worry!  My theory will work.  It's been...  OW!"<br />
<br />
Da bixie easily caught up with da slower halfling and stung him right in da arm.  Even da bixie couldn't believe how stupid dis particular halfling was.  Realizing dat maybe his idea might not be as brilliant as he had thought, Lilting opted to do what druids do best:  Run away like mad.<br />
<br />
"Let's get out of here!  Ow!  Ow!" Lilting said turning to his friend, but Nappyhair had long since bolted away.  Lilting started to make a run for his home, but it was slow-going because of his ensnare spell.<br />
<br />
<br />
********<br />
<br />
<br />
Back in Rivervale, an out-of-breath Nappyhair explained to Lilting's parents what happened.<br />
<br />
"What are we to do with our son?" asked Mama Lildruid.  "He doesn't seem to want to learn our ways."<br />
<br />
"I guess we'll just have to punish him.  Again." Daddy Lildruid was disappointed his only son wouldn't learn da art of being a druid.  "How far behind you was he, Nappyhair?"<br />
<br />
"Well, uh," stammered Nappyhair, "I think he, uh, was right behind me."<br />
<br />
Suddenly a faint noise could be heard coming from just outside da city gates.  "Ow!"  It progressively became louder.  "Ow!"  Many halflings exited deir homes to see what dis noise was and crowded around the center of da town.<br />
<br />
Coming over da ridge, a very stung and very slow Lilting jogged towards his parents.  Just behind him was da mean bixie who kept stinging his backside.  "Ow!  Ow!  Ow!  Ow!"  Lilting kept yelping.<br />
<br />
Daddy Lildruid came to da rescue and swatted da bixie away.  "Get out of here!"  Da bixie just made a laughing, buzzing sound at Lilting and left da way it came.<br />
<br />
"Now, young man," Daddy Lildruid began, "What were you thinking?!"<br />
<br />
"I wanted to try..."<br />
<br />
"You wanted to get yourself killed!" Mama Lildruid scolded.  "Why do you have to try different things?  We're druids!  We cast, and then we run away!  We cast again, and then we run away again!  Anything else is suicide!"<br />
<br />
Da gathered crowd of halfling villagers all nodded deir agreement at what da boy's mother had said.  Dis was da art of kiting first invented by da halfling legend, Kiter McTerrified.<br />
<br />
"Son," his father told Lilting sternly while placing a hand on his shoulder, "I'm going to have to punish you until you learn.  No supper for you tonight."<br />
<br />
"Nooooo!!!  Dad, please, no!  Anything but that!  Anything!"<br />
<br />
"Hold on, I say, Hold on here!"  A voice from da crowd rose up.  A halfling pushed his way through da crowd.  He was older dan da rest of da halflings, fatter too.  "Now what is, I say, what is the problem here?"<br />
<br />
"Mayor McFurrybottom!"  Daddy Lildruid said in astonishment.  "There's no problem.  Well, nothing too big.  It's my son, your honor.  He rejects our standard druid ways and tried a new fighting tactic.  He trained a bixie into town."<br />
<br />
"Is that so?  Bixies, eh?  Nasty little, I say, nasty little buggers.  Can't have them running around town.  Certainly not."  Da crowd of halflings shook deir heads in agreement, wit several others repeating "Certainly not."<br />
<br />
"None of you understand," Lilting began, "I feel that druids are capable of much more than what we know!  I think that we can become one of the land's most respected people and not just a running gag!"<br />
<br />
"Nonsense, my boy," da Mayor said in disbelief,  "We druids have survived hundreds of years by holding dear to the truths and teachings of our beloved Kiter McTerrified!  We will continue to do for hundreds of years more.  Running away is what we do best!"<br />
<br />
"Well, maybe I'm tired of running away!" Lilting said wit tears of anger and frustration welling up inside him.  "Maybe I want to use a weapon now and then!"<br />
<br />
Mama Lildruid snapped a hand up to her mouth in utter horror at what her son had just said.  Da crowd of halflings gasped in shock and began whispering amongst demselves.<br />
<br />
"Maybe I want to actually use spells like thorn skin!" Lilting said defiantly.<br />
<br />
Mama Lildruid's second hand snapped up to her mouth.   Louder gasps and whispers came from da crowd.<br />
<br />
"And maybe I want to shave my foot hair from time to time!"<br />
<br />
Mama Lildruid's eyes rolled back into her head and she fainted.  Daddy Lildruid could stand to hear no more. <br />
<br />
"Blasphemy!" said Daddy.  "Son, I'm going to pretend I didn't hear that!  I'm going to pretend the bee stings on your backside are causing you to think irrationally!  Look what you did to your mother! Go to your room this instant!"<br />
<br />
"One more thing, dad." said Lilting.  "Maybe I want to actually join a group when I go out fighting."<br />
<br />
"That's it, boy," Mayor McFurrybottom said wit a finger pointed straight at Lilting, "You're a bad seed.  Thoughts like that will destroy this town!  You bring a nasty bixie here today, what will you bring tomorrow with these foolhardy ideas?  A bear?  A giant?!  I hearby decree that you shall be banned from this city for a period of no less than 3 months!  If being out on your own doesn't teach you that our ways are the correct ways, nothing will!"<br />
<br />
"Sir, I..."<br />
<br />
"Go!" da mayor pointed towards da gates of da city.  Da crowd all nodded in agreement with the mayor.  Each halfling had a scowl on their face and waited impatiently for Lilting to leave.<br />
<br />
"Son," Daddy Lildruid said wit restraint, "I think this is for the best.  Please do as the Mayor says.  And please remember our teachings.  They will keep you alive.  Don't be a fool and try to change them.  Now, please go.  Your mother and I will await your return."<br />
<br />
"Dad, I just..."<br />
<br />
"Please, son.  For your mother, for me, for yourself.  Just go."<br />
<br />
And without another word, Lilting turned around and slowly walked out of Rivervale.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
