<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>It was da middle of da night and all was silent in Oggok.  Well, all was silent except for all da loud snoring coming from every single ogre cave in dat town, and da loud scraping sound made whenever da guards needed to scratch demselves.  Udder dan dat dough, all was quiet.<br />
<br />
On his bed dat was made of a big slab of rock, Bash slept uneasily.  He always had nightmares of what he feared may have happened to Smash on his journey.  It had been a year since he saw him last and Bash worried he may no have killed Smellybreath.<br />
<br />
A very loud *THUD* woke Bash up with startle.  Bash looked over to see Papa Smurpheater on da floor cursing someting about it being too dark during night time.<br />
<br />
"Grandpa!" said Bash as he jumped out bed to help da old ogre up. "Is yous ok?  What you doing in me room dis late?"<br />
<br />
Grandpa rubbed da side of his face for a few seconds and den spoke.  "Well, Moondoggy, I wake up because I had the munch...er.. I was hungry.  So I stumble into the kitchen to grab a bite to eat.  Well, I accidentally grabbed the Sacred Peyote and didn't know it.  I took a huge bite and swallowed it down."<br />
<br />
Bash hoped his grandpa wasn't going to die.  He never seen him so sick and wobbly before.<br />
<br />
"The funny thing is," said Papa, "I found out that I've been using the Sacred Peyote wrong all these years.  You're not supposed to smoke it!  It was a groovy experience, man."<br />
<br />
"Well, what happened?!"<br />
<br />
"Hmmm... let me think... it's all a little fuzzy.  Well, naturechild, I think your brother's not coming back anytime soon.  And I think he may even be in danger.  The Details are a bit funny.  I do know this though:  You must go to Halas."<br />
<br />
"Halas?!" Bash said in complete shock.  "But dat is farthest away place of anywhere in dis world!  What is me supposed to do dere?!  Buy a kilt?!"<br />
<br />
"Settle down, hip cat."  Papa said wit his hands raised.  "You need to head to that land of uncool coldness to talk the one person who can tell you where to find your brother."<br />
<br />
"And who would dat be?"<br />
<br />
"I have no idea.  I just know he's hanging around Halas.  That's what my vision said."<br />
<br />
"And is dat all?"<br />
<br />
"No, it said that if you find people willing to help you along your journey, that you should let them.  Maybe even go out of your way to ask a few people.  If I had not smoked the Peyote last time, I bet the same would have applied to your brother.  Stupid me.  I should have realized that trying to solo in this world is the second dumbest thing there is."<br />
<br />
"What's da first dumbest ting?"<br />
<br />
"Answering a female ogre when she asks, 'Do yous tink me hips look fatter now dan before?' instead of running away.  There is no way to answer that question without getting several broken bones."<br />
<br />
"Hmmm.  Me remember dat.  Is dat all da visions yous had?"<br />
<br />
"Yep.  Well, after all that I did have a good conversation with a purple camel and a very foul-mouthed rock.  But it wasn't anything important.  Something about 'A Banshee and sock puppets.'"<br />
<br />
"Ok den.  Me will leave in da morning for Halas.  Me was having good dream about dat cute ogre girl in da Shaman guild."<br />
<br />
"No no!  You have to leave tonight!"<br />
<br />
"Why?"<br />
<br />
"Because that was part of my vision."<br />
<br />
"You said dat was all..."<br />
<br />
"Yeah yeah.  Shut up.  You have to leave tonight or else..."<br />
<br />
"...Da donkey and da ice cream?"<br />
<br />
"You got it."  Papa reached into his tunic and pulled out some coins. "Here, take these and buy some food for your journey.  And also..."<br />
<br />
Papa walked to the other end of the room and opened up a secret, false-rock panel.  He pulled out a gigantic, gold-plated mallet.<br />
<br />
"I want you to take this.  I should have given it to your brother, but I was too stoned to remember it.  This hammer has seen many adventuring days in our family and has squished many an orc head.  It is said that if the right ogre were to ever wield it...  Ah, I can't remember the rest."<br />
<br />
Bash's eyes were wide open, staring at da most beautiful hammer he ever seen.  He thought he was not worthy of such a ting.<br />
<br />
"Grandpa... me... me no can take dis."<br />
<br />
"Yes you can, and yes you will.  I can't smoke it, so what good does it do me anymore?  Besides, you may need it for some nasty, harrowing, climactic escape or battle.  Now, get out here.  There's little time to waste!"<br />
<br />
Bash gently took da mallet from Papa's hands with awe and reverence.  He den hugged his grandfather and left da house he and his brudder had been raised in for several years.  Bash stopped at da 24 hour ogre store near da Oggok entrance to buy some rations and den set off on his journey.<br />
<br />
Bash jogged down da road dat lead southeast in da Feerrott swamp.  Swatting at buzzing mosquitoes and stomping on da occasional snake for fun, he made good time.  An hour or so down da road he noticed dat da sun was starting to come up. <br />
<br />
Bash stopped as he saw a small lizard camp dat he knew well.  He saw da three lizardmen warming demselves around a fire dat he and Smash used to beat upon to help demselves train.  He smiled.<br />
<br />
Da lizardmen all looked up at da same time and saw Bash wit a wicked grin on his face.  Den dey saw da big, golden hammer da ogre was carrying.  Dey looked at each udder, and den dey immediately scattered in all directions to hide from da ogre dey remembered all-too-well.<br />
<br />
Bash frowned.  Da lizards no wanted to play.  He sighed and prepared to continue onward, but he heard a noise come from somewhere above him.<br />
<br />
"I'm a tree!  I'm a tree!  I'm a..." Da snapping and cracking of a branch was heard shortly after da voice was interrupted.<br />
<br />
Bash scratched his head in puzzlement and a few seconds later he saw a blond halfling fall from da sky and land wit a loud *THUMP* in front of him.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
