<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Bash looked at da unconscious halfling dat lay in front of him on da forest road.  He said many 'tank yous' to his god, Da Warlord, for giving him such a fine meal dis day.  He bent over and picked up da halfling, opened his mouth and prepared to take a big bite.<br />
<br />
Da halfling awoke just as his little head was inside da big ogre's mouth.  A muffled scream came from inside Bash's throat.<br />
<br />
"Pleesh donf eaf mef!!!"<br />
<br />
Bash pulled da halfling out of his mouth.  "What did yous call me?!"<br />
<br />
"I said," the frightened halfling stammered, "'Please don't eat me!'"<br />
<br />
"Why?  Yous look like a good meal.  Me is hungry.  Me have long journey ahead of me and me need da protein."<br />
<br />
"But...  But I can help you!"  The halfling would do anything at this point to get out of being eaten.  "You need someone to carry that big hammer for you on your journey?  You need someone to help you fight whatever it is you need fighting?  You need anyone to slay some mean wizards or someth..."<br />
<br />
"Wizards?  What yous know about wizards?"  Bash was intrigued.  Maybe he stumbled upon a ting who knew where Smellybreath was.<br />
<br />
"Nothing other than they use magic.  I was just saying I could help..."<br />
<br />
Den again, maybe not.  But Bash remembered what his grandpa said about letting peoples join his group if he meet peoples who is willing.  He decided to give it a shot.<br />
<br />
"Ok den.  Yous can come along wit me and me will no eat yous.  Me name is Bash Emgood."<br />
<br />
"Great!" The halfling became excited and relieved at the same time.  Maybe Lilting will be able to do something to prove dat druids is more dan what everyone tinks on dis journey.  "My name is Lilting.  So where are we headed and what are we doing when we get there?"<br />
<br />
"Us is going to Halas.  And when we get dere, us is looking for a person me grandpa told me about who can tell us where me brudder is so us can find a goblin who bashed our parents and den bash it and come back and be done."<br />
<br />
Lilting just blinked in confusion.<br />
<br />
"Us is going to Halas."<br />
<br />
"Ok!  Well, let's get going!  I hope you don't have anything against druids because I am one."<br />
<br />
Bash's urge to eat da halfling resurfaced.  He did his best to stifle it.  <i>At least</i>, Bash thought, <i>he'll be able to haul his little butt away from any danger.  Me will no have to protect him too much.  Dat is good.</i><br />
<br />
"However," Lilting began, "I'm not like most druids.  I don't believe in using the same tactics every other druid employs."<br />
<br />
<i>So much for dat.</i><br />
<br />
"Well, let's get going!" the enthusiastic halfling excalimed excitedly.  "Can I carry that big hammer of yours?"<br />
<br />
"No."<br />
<br />
"Can I ride on your shoulders?"<br />
<br />
"No."<br />
<br />
"Can I sing some traveling songs?"<br />
<br />
"No."<br />
<br />
"Can I pick fights with everything that passes us by because you'll pound them?"<br />
<br />
"No."<br />
<br />
"Can I..."<br />
<br />
Da questions of da halfling trailed off as dey headed east towards da murky, foul, Innothule Swamp.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
