	<!-- /1 -->
	
	</td>
	<td class="thead">
	
	<!-- 2 -->
	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		
		<td class="smallfont"><b>Chapter 6.</b></td>
		<td class="smallfont" align="right" wrap="nowrap">Post #<b><a href="showpost.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;postid=8998&postcount=6" target="new">6</a></b></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	<!-- /2 -->
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Da big ogre and tiny halfling made it to da pass dat lead to da swamp in just half a day.  Once through, dey found da swamp was thicker, muckier, and more stinky dan normal.<br />
<br />
"Can I run circles around you for excercise?"<br />
<br />
"No."<br />
<br />
"Can I hop up and down instead of just normal hiking?"<br />
<br />
"No."<br />
<br />
"Can I..."  Da smell of da swamp hit da halfling's nose.<br />
<br />
"Ewww!  This place is gross!" a very disgusted Lilting said as he placed his hand up to cover his mouth and nose.  "How long do we have to endure this?"<br />
<br />
"You not know?" Bash asked curiously.  "Didn't yous come through swamp to get to da lovely Feerrott?"<br />
<br />
"Well, uh, no." da halfling said nervously.  You see, I, uh... well... I tried to teach myself to teleport but in an unconventional way.  To make a long story short..."<br />
<br />
"Save it.  Me tink me hear someting."<br />
<br />
Through the dense fog and trees covered wit vines, Bash thought he could see a lot of movement.  He figured da sounds he heard came from dere, so he decided to head towards it.<br />
<br />
"Nuh uh!" a defiant Lilting said.  "I'm not wading through that muck!  You can just go on without me!"<br />
<br />
Da next sound heard was da splash of water about as loud as a splash dat a halfling makes when thrown by an ogre into a murky bog.<br />
<br />
Bash and Lilting trudged through the thick slime for about an hour until Bash spotted da ting he saw from da pass.  A large group of green, stinky trolls were huddled together in a large circle cheering and hooting about someting.  Bash decided to get a closer look.<br />
<br />
"Are you crazy?!"  Lilting was not happy about going to meet a bunch of stinky trolls.  "They'll eat us alive!"<br />
<br />
"No dey won't."  Bash said. Lilting's face became washed wit relief.  "Dey will only eat yous.  Trolls no mess wit us big ogres."  <br />
<br />
Lilting's face contorted wit fear again.<br />
<br />
"But no worry.  Just don't talk and yous be fine.  Me have idea if trolls ask questions.  If anyone is gonna eat yous, it gonna be me!"  <br />
<br />
Lilting thought dat was good, but wasn't sure.<br />
<br />
Da ogre and halfling approached da trolls cautiously.  Da trolls were excited about someting in da center of deir circle.  Dey were throwing gold pieces all over the place in da center.  Bash and Smash no could see into da circle of trolls because da green, smelly tings were tightly packed together.  Bash pulled one troll aside to ask some questions.<br />
<br />
"Hey, dumbhead," said Bash with authority and intimidation, "What is going on in dere?"<br />
<br />
Da troll looked back and forth with a little bit of fear.  Not wanting to get involved wit an ogre, and also wanting to get back to whatever it was he was doing, he decided to just answer da ogres questions quickly.<br />
<br />
"Miz iz warchin dim barsh gud!  Us trows monies at chumin ilf gud barsher.  Miz maykz lotz uv monies!  Himz barsh de froggo bist miz evur see!"  Da troll, not wanting to waste more time talking to da ogre, turned around and begain cheering some more.<br />
<br />
Lilting raised one eyebrow in complete confusion.<br />
<br />
"What did he say?" whispered da halfling to da ogre.<br />
<br />
"He said dat dere is a human-elf in dere who can bash frogloks better dan anyting he ever seen before.  Me guess da trolls is betting money on who will win, and he made tons of money from betting on human-elf.  Me guess it never lost yet."<br />
<br />
"I want to see!" da halfling said excitedly.<br />
<br />
"Yous is too short to see over da trolls."<br />
<br />
"Not if you pick me up!"<br />
<br />
"Hmmm.  Dat true.  Maybe dat good idea and yous tell me what yous see."  And wit dat, da ogre picked up da halfling and held him high over da heads of da trolls.<br />
<br />
What Lilting saw was two beings locked in a fight. Both a froglok and a light brown-haired half-elf were circling around each other, waiting for da udder to strike.  Da froglok wore chainmail and was holding an axe. Da half-elf wore leather armor with udder bits and pieces of green cloth all over  da place (but nothing on his head) and wielded a longsword in one hand and a forward-curved short sword in da udder. <br />
<br />
Da froglok attacked first.  It swung its axe in a chopping motion towards da half-elf.  Da half-elf easily dodged and parried da blow down to da ground.  Da froglok lifted its axe and swung at da half-elf. It was easily parried wit one sword as anudder stabbed da froglok in da arm.  Da froglok went into a frenzy and swung wildly at da half-elf.  His axe was blocked again and forced downward to touch da ground again.  Da half-elf brought up his short sword in a blinding rush and caused da froglok to try and dodge.  As soon as da froglok did, dough, da half-elf switched directions wit his short sword and den spun around in a quick flash and stabbed da froglok wit his longsword straight through its head.  Da froglock fell over in a lump and da trolls cheered and roared.<br />
<br />
Lilting watched da whole ting in amazement.  Da fight was over in a blink of an eye and never before did he ever see such skill and speed in a swordsman.  <br />
<br />
Da trolls in one part of the circle spread apart to let anudder troll walk in.  Dis troll was carrying a bigger, meaner looking froglok.  He set it down and joined da udder trolls.  Da trolls formed a tight circle again.<br />
<br />
Da froglock, not wanting to be away from its home any longer dan needed, began attacking da half-elf right away.  But instead of using a weapon, it started to cast fireball spells at da half-elf.  Da half-elf was quick dough, and dodged back and forth avoiding da fireballs.  Leaping and rolling, he moved closer towards da froglok.<br />
<br />
Da froglok summoned more power dis time and its hand glowed brighter dan before.  It shot out a massive fireball towards da half-elf.  Da half-elf leaped high and did a flip towards da froglock.  At da end of his spin, and before he touched da ground, he stabbed da froglock wit his longsword and den sliced downwards wit his shortsword, splitting da frog's head in two vertical pieces.<br />
<br />
Landing and den pulling his swords out sharply, da half-elf watched as da froglok just slumped to da ground next to a dozen or so udder froglok corpses.  Da trolls roared and cheered even louder dan before.<br />
<br />
"What is going on in dere?!" Bash asked quickly.  "What do yous see?!"<br />
<br />
"I see....  Wow!  This guy is amazing!"  Lilting was too awestruck and breathtaken to find words.  "He killed them all."<br />
<br />
"Who did?  A troll?"<br />
<br />
"Wow.  That wizard had no chance at all!"<br />
<br />
"Wizard?!"  Bash became excited at da thought of someting being able to kill a wizard.  Bash needed whatever's help was in dat circle of trolls.  He got an idea.<br />
<br />
At da top of his lungs, Bash shouted.  "Me saw Jocka da female troll outside of Grobb entrance skinny dipping in da swamp!  She said someting about free food to da first 3 'cute' trolls to come see her!"<br />
<br />
Da entire group of trolls immmediately shut up and turned towards da ogre.  Den, each at da exact same time, turned deir heads in da same direction looking off into da swamp somwhere.  A split second later, da trolls were running off into da swamp at extreme speed.  Well, fast for trolls anyway.<br />
<br />
Looking downward and brushing himself off, da half-elf started to talk.  "Thanks for that, I didn't think they were going to let me go anytime soon."  Da half-elf looked up and saw da ogre holding a halfling in one hand.  Swords instantly came up.<br />
<br />
"Leave me alone, big one!  I'm sure you'll kill me, but I'll go down with a fight!"<br />
<br />
"Me don't want to kill yous.  Me want yous help.  Us is looking to kill a goblin wizard and we need someone like yous."<br />
<br />
A little confused, da half-elf furrowed his brow and just stared at da ogre.<br />
<br />
"It's true!" Lilting piped up.  "He hasn't eaten me and it's been almost a full day since we met!  I'm pretty sure he's telling the truth!  You were amazing in there!"<br />
<br />
"Well, I was <b>this</b> close to being killed.  Had I been in there one more minute, I'd be dead right now!"<br />
<br />
"What are you talking about?  You were wiping the floor with them!"  da halfling said not believing dis half-elf.<br />
<br />
"I was brushing near death each time!"<br />
<br />
"You didn't even get a scratch!"<br />
<br />
"I was lucky.  Had you not come along..."<br />
<br />
"Why didn't you just kill the trolls and be done with it?"<br />
<br />
"Because, I knew I was going to get killed any time now.  It's a miracle I've lived this long.  I figured I might as well go out a hero."<br />
<br />
Bash had enough of da question and answer session.  "Look, will yous help us or not?  Us is in kind of a hurry."<br />
<br />
Da half-elf considered it for a minute.  "Well, I'm <b>positive</b> I'll be slain within a day and won't be much good to you.  But, I've got nothing better to do while waiting for my inevitable death.  Sure, why not?"<br />
<br />
"Ok den.  Us need a good elf fighter."<br />
<br />
"I am <b>not</b> an elf or a fighter!  I'm a half-elf ranger!  Fighters can at least survive their fights!"<br />
<br />
"But you just surviv..." Lilting began but was interrupted by Bash.<br />
<br />
"Ok den.  Me is Bash Emgood and dis is Lilting.  Us is going to Halas and we need to get going now."<br />
<br />
"All right.  My name is Treehugger."<br />
<br />
And wit dat, da three of dem trudged northward in da swamp.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
