	</td>
	<td class="thead">
	
	<!-- 2 -->
	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		
		<td class="smallfont"><b>Chapter 9.</b></td>
		<td class="smallfont" align="right" wrap="nowrap">Post #<b><a href="showpost.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;postid=9001&postcount=9" target="new">9</a></b></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	<!-- /2 -->
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Da party moved northward through the desert.  Reaching da northern side of da oasis in Oasis dey stopped at a merchant's tent for some supplies.<br />
<br />
"So just where exactly are we going?" asked Medsa in her usual over-authoritative brash way.<br />
<br />
"Halas!" said an excited Lilting after having just purchased some lip balm.  "It's gonna be fun!"<br />
<br />
"<b>HALAS?!?!!</b>" said a not-so-calm cleric.  Turning to Treehugger, she asked, again in a not-so-calm fashion,"What in the 3 planes and 3 unreleased planes of existence made you think that I'd enjoy that frost-ridden, savage-infested, slippery, slushy, iced hell-hole of a waste of space on this planet?!?!"<br />
<br />
A little more than afraid, Treehugger bowed his head in silence.  Den, he remembered someting and said, "Well, I did say that we were going to a place that is nothing at all like this desert."<br />
<br />
Medsa just sneered at da ranger but didn't say anyting.  Treehugger just winked back.<br />
<br />
"Listen, tiny lady," Bash joined in, "Us is on an important quest.  Us needs to stop a powerful goblin wizard."<br />
<br />
"From doing what?"<br />
<br />
"Ummm... us just needs to stop him, ok?!  If yous want to go back to heal da losers den just go.  Yous not need to waste our time and insult me friends."<br />
<br />
Medsa considered da ogre's words.  But, den she looked back half a mile and still saw da line of peoples waiting to be healed.  Da peoples were still looking around not knowing what to do, while some where just looking in her direction.  She thought she could still see some crying.  Da cleric decided dat life was not for her and maybe she needed to go on dis adventure after all.  Maybe it would be nice to have some friends for a change.<br />
<br />
"Fine!  I'll go on your lame little voyage. But I'm just doing it because I feel sorry for you pathetic people!  Always remember that!"<br />
<br />
"Ok den.  Let's get moving."<br />
<br />
Just den, dey all heard a loud, deep scream of terror.  Dey turned around to see a big, mean Sand Giant running from a tiny skeleton.<br />
<br />
"Help!  Help!  It's gonna kill me!" da Sand Giant yelled as it came near da group.  It stopped in front of Bash and pleaded.  "It's gonna kill me!  He's gonna kill me!  Please help!"<br />
<br />
Da skeleton caught up to da giant and laughed.  It poked da giant in da ankle.<br />
<br />
"Ow!  Ow!" da Giant cried.  And den, a split second later, it fell over dead.<br />
<br />
Da skeleton laughed again and did a Pee-Wee Herman dance with a bit of disco thrown in for good measure.  Over da hill, a tiny gnome came running up to da dead giant.  Da gnome had white hair, a big nose, and a brown robe.<br />
<br />
"Good work, Jakontiklarkiak!  Here's a skellie snack!" da gnome said as he pulled out a green and blue box dat had da words 'Skellie Snacks' on da front.  He took out a brown cookie-like object and tossed it to da skeleton.  <br />
<br />
Da skeleton jumped up in da air and caught it in it's mouth and swallowed it.  When da skeleton landed, da cookie crumbs just went through its ribcage and landed on da sandy floor.  Da skeleton no seemed to mind or even notice.<br />
<br />
Treehugger looked at da gnome and skeleton and rolled his eyes.  "Oh great," he said, "A necromancer."<br />
<br />
Da whole group rolled deir eyes and moaned at da news.<br />
<br />
Da gnome bent over da giant's corpse and took some loose change from its pocket.  A split second later, da giant disappeared in a puff of smoke.<br />
<br />
Da gnome stood up and noticed da group. <br />
<br />
"Hi guys!" da gnome said.  Seeing da supplies in hand dat da party just purchased, da gnome became curious. "What are you fellows up to?"<br />
<br />
"Nuttin'." Bash said quickly.  "Yous can go back to giant killing now."<br />
<br />
Realizing what was going on, da gnome excitedly said, "You're going on an adventure!  Oh boy!  That sounds like it's going to be fun!  Oh boy oh boy!"<br />
<br />
Da gnome started jumping up and down wit excited glee.  Da skeleton looked at da gnome, shrugged, and started jumping up and down too.<br />
<br />
With fingers in his ears, Lilting shouted, "Can you please stop doing that?!  That rattling from the skeleton is making my ears hurt!"<br />
<br />
Da gnome stopped jumping and den da skeleton did too.<br />
<br />
"My name is Philiac, but you can just call me Phil."  Pointing to da skeleton, da gnome said, "And this here is Jakontiklarkiak."<br />
<br />
Hearing his name and seeing his master point at him, da skeleton wasn't really listening to what had been said so it just started to do 'da moonwalk' and ended wit a spin.<br />
<br />
Da group half-heartedly clapped.  Jakontiklarkiak bowed for da applause.<br />
<br />
"Listen, we both were wondering if you would like to have a necromancer and a skeleton along for the ride." da gnome said.<br />
<br />
Da group looked at da gnome, and den each member of da party turned deir heads to da skeleton.  Da skeleton just pointed at da gnome, shook its head and shrugged at da party.<br />
<br />
"Ummm... look, us appreciate da offer but..." Bash began.<br />
<br />
"I'm really powerful!  Look how I took down that giant!  I can kill anything!"<br />
<br />
"We're sure you can but..." Treehugger said.<br />
<br />
"I've got more money than everyone in Norrath combined!"<br />
<br />
"That's nice but..." Lilting started.<br />
<br />
"I've got three banks-worth full of ultra-uniquely rare items!"<br />
<br />
"Dat's great, but, why would yous want to join us if yous have all dat?  Us is not in dis for da money or da items.  Well, me is not." Bash said.<br />
<br />
"Because," Phil said, "Well.... You see.... Well...."<br />
<br />
"Yes?" da party said.<br />
<br />
"Well, I'm.... I'm lonely.  All I do is sit here waiting for the next giant to arrive so I can kill it dead.  Then I wait some more.  And then I kill some more.  And then I wait some more." da gnome started to sniff some tears back.<br />
<br />
"Nobody wants to be my friend.  Nobody wants to date me.  All this power, and no one to share or frighten it with."<br />
<br />
Da skeleton nodded at da party and den made a 'L' shape wit his hand and stuck it up to its forehead looking at da gnome.  Phil wasn't paying attention.<br />
<br />
"Me is sorry," said Bash, "But yous is just a necromancer.  Us is not wanting... er... needing a necromancer right now."<br />
<br />
"PLEEEEEASE?!" da gnome said desperately throwing himself at da ogre's big feet.  Stench overpowering, da gnome backed up a little bit.  "Oh please oh please oh please let me join!  You have no idea how boring it is having my life!  Please please please let me join!"<br />
<br />
Phil began to sob uncontrollably and his whole face seemed to leak.  Da gnome used part of his robe to blow his nose on.<br />
<br />
One eyebrow raised, Bash looked at da skeleton for an answer.  Da skeleton just shrugged.<br />
<br />
Treehugger had an idea.  "Say, what if we said that we'd let you in the group when Hate freezes over?"<br />
<br />
Sniffling, da gnome said "You... *sniff* guys would *sniff*  do that for me?"<br />
<br />
"Sure we would!" da ranger said looking to da party for some false support.<br />
<br />
Da whole group nodded with eyebrows raised and big smiles all around.<br />
<br />
"*Sniff*... you guys *sniff* are the greatest!  *Sniff*  Come on Jakontiklarkiak, let' go bag us some more worthless platinum pieces!"<br />
<br />
And wit dat, da gnome smiled and waved to da party and was trotting off in da desert.  Da skeleton, mockingly rubbed his eyes like it was crying and pointed at da running gnome and den laughed.  It looked at da party, shurgged again, waved goodbye, and den ran off after da gnome.<br />
<br />
"Necromancers," said Medsa, "Not the brightest bunch."<br />
<br />
"Us almost had one in our group!" da big ogre said.<br />
<br />
Everyone shuddered.<br />
<br />
Da party snickered some at da gnome now too small to see from dis distance, and den headed northward towards da town of Freeport.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
