	</td>
	<td class="thead">
	
	<!-- 2 -->
	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		
		<td class="smallfont"><b>Chapter 10.</b></td>
		<td class="smallfont" align="right" wrap="nowrap">Post #<b><a href="showpost.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;postid=9002&postcount=10" target="new">10</a></b></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	<!-- /2 -->
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>In a thick cloud of red fog, a demon sat on a throne made of bones from different races.  Da red fog surrounded everyting as far as da eye could see.  Moans and wails of pain and suffering could be heard from unseen captives in dis dense, nasty haze.  Dis was da Plane of Pain.<br />
<br />
Adjusting his huge black wings jutting from his red, scaly body, da demon made himself more comfortable in his chair.  Pure white eyes stared off in da distance in pleasure as he listened to da harmonious sounds of da tortured souls in his "care."  Blood stained fangs jutted out from both upper and lower jaws and curved into a smile.  Dis was his home.  Dis was his paradise.<br />
<br />
Some people said dat da souls were screaming in pain because of da eternal fire dat is scorching deir bodies.  Some say it is because of da mourning of a life dat dey screwed up.  But most say it's because of da demon's favorite music dat is piped in throughout da Plane -- music made by an elf named Yanni.<br />
<br />
Da Plane of Pain is where dumbheads go when dey die.  If yous did sometime particularly stupid, den you ended up here.  All da people who claimed to have seen da Lake Rathe Monster were here.  All da people who ever typed da words "sow" or "plz" were here.  And all da peoples who shout conversations across vast areas were here.  Dey didn't like it much.<br />
<br />
Nodding his head in-time to a particularly torturous melody, da demon noticed green smoke starting to form at da foot of his throne.  Realizing he was about to have company and not wanting dem to know his secret admiration of dat elf's music, da demon pressed a button on his throne dat made Yanni's music disappear and some heavy sounds pipe through from an ogre group named Savatage.  Interestingly enough, da captured souls sounded a bit more happy.<br />
<br />
Da smoke cleared and da image of a robed figure was standing before da demon.  Da demon couldn't see da figure's face, but he knew who it was.  Da demon had dealt wit dis person in da past.<br />
<br />
"Ahhh, good old, Killdead." da robed figure said.  "I see you're back to your usual self and enjoying the fruits of your office."<br />
<br />
"No easy thanks to you." da demon grumbled in a low, gutteral, hissing voice.  "Speak what you need and then get out of here!"<br />
<br />
Da shade laughed a ****y laugh.  "I'll stay for as long as I choose!  You have very little power over me."<br />
<br />
Da demons eyes turned into mere slits with hatred towards da shadow.  He knew it to be true.<br />
<br />
"Now, I came here to ask of your assistance." da figure said.<br />
<br />
"You've already forced me to grant your one wish, fool!  Remember?!" Killdead da demon was quaking with rage.  "You asked for power beyond that of my own and inso doing got your wish but reduced me to weaker state whilst you gained abilities your kind could only dream!"<br />
<br />
"That is quite true.  I'm not sure why you just reminded me of that bit of history because I obviously know it.  But who knows what demon logic is like, eh?<br />
<br />
"No I have come here to ask of one and only one favor.  In return, I shall grant you some of your former power back and also never bug you again."<br />
<br />
"Never?"<br />
<br />
"Never."<br />
<br />
"Not even on my birthday?"<br />
<br />
"Nope."<br />
<br />
"Not even when you want to show off your newest Pokemon trading cards?"<br />
<br />
"Not even then."<br />
<br />
"You have got yourself a deal!  I will do anything to be rid of you.  What is that you would have me do?"<br />
<br />
"There is a group of adventurers heading towards the barbarian home lands.  I do not know exactly where they are or just who these people are themselves, but I do know they must be destroyed.  Demons are the best at that sort of thing, so naturally I thought of you.  Kill them all, and you will be free to do as you wish without me in your life to bug you again."<br />
<br />
"Sweeeet!" Killdead excalimed.  "I'll have to do some tracking once I get down to the mortal Plane since you've robbed me of my demonic finding power, but it shouldn't be that difficult.  Now, once they're gone, you promise I'll never see you again?"<br />
<br />
"I promise."<br />
<br />
"Do the eternal damnation soul oath." da demon said wit a smile.  Dat oath no character could break.  Good or evil.<br />
<br />
Da shade sighed and den placed his right hand on his head.  And den his left hand.  And den placed his right hand on his hip, followed by his left.  And den he stuck his right hand straight out, and den his left.  Den he put both hands on his hips and moved his rear around in a circular motion while ending wit da sacred chant,  "Haaay Mock-a Ray-Na!"<br />
<br />
Satisfied, Killdead smiled his approval.  "I will set off for those pathetic souls tonight.  Now, if you don't mind..."<br />
<br />
"Gotcha.  I'm gone.  Do as I ask, or you'll be seeing a lot more of me.  A lot more.  And I just got my Ultra-Platinum Limited Edition Pikachu Trading Card Series that I'm dying show somebody."<br />
<br />
Da demon shuddered wit revulsion and made a silent vow dat it would complete dis quest or die trying.  Shortly after, da shadow disappeared in a puff of green smoke.<br />
<br />
Switching his music back to Yanni and hearing da screams of anger, hatred, and ultimate pain begin again, da demon settled back comfortably into his chair.  He wanted to relish every last bit of scream and music before he took flight to da mortal plane.<br />
<br />
Closing his eyes and lips turning into a contented smile, da demon just contemplated etnernity one last time.  One last thought occured to him before he finally left his throne.<br />
<br />
<i>"You know, even that guy's shade has really, really bad breath."</i></p>
	
	
	
	
	
