<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Bash's group made it to da gates of Freeport wit not too many problems.  Well, unless you consider constant whining about having to go to da bathroom by Lilting a problem.  Or da constant pick-up lines Treehugger was dishing out a problem.  Or da fact dat Medsa got fed up and kicked Treehugger wit extreme force in his "lower area" and let him suffer a bit before healing him up a problem.  No, it was a pretty smooth journey.<br />
<br />
"Halt!  Who goes there?!" a fully armored person standing in front of da Freeport gate asked.<br />
<br />
"Yes!  State your business now or be cut down  where you stand!" said da udder fully armored person standing in front of da gate.<br />
<br />
"Hail, friend guards." Treehugger said.  "We come to the city for supplies and information.  No trouble walks with us."<br />
<br />
"You speak the words, ranger, but what of that big fellow behind you?" da guard said pointing to Bash suspiciously.  "He looks like an ogre.  Ogres are to be killed on sight!"<br />
<br />
Bash's face became an expression of anger.  He wanted to squish dis little human wit his hammer.  Treehugger quickly interjected.<br />
<br />
"An ogre?!" Da ranger laughed.  "What would I be doing with an ogre?!  Besides, you intelligent guards would have seen an ogre coming from miles away, right?"<br />
<br />
Da guards looked at each udder and nodded deir agreement.  "Yes, that is correct.  Nothing gets by us!" said da first guard.  "Quite right!  We are trained from childhood to detect such things!" said da udder guard.<br />
<br />
"Exactly.  Now, if you would let us pass, we'd like to enter.  We're on urgent business." da ranger said wit a smile.<br />
<br />
"Very good.  In you go.  Hurry along now." da guard said.  Da group not wanting to waste any more time began to march through the gate when all of a sudden one of da guards spoke up.<br />
<br />
"Wait a minute!  Something's not quite right here."<br />
<br />
"Yes, I sense it too." said da udder guard.<br />
<br />
Bash looked uncomfortably at Treehugger, and da ranger just looked back with uneasiness.<br />
<br />
"There!!  There!!  I see it!!" said da first guard.<br />
<br />
"Yes! Yes!" da udder guard said.  "<b>SNAKE!  SNAKE!</b>  To arms! brothers, to arms!"<br />
<br />
Da two guards rushed passed da party and ran out into da field where a tiny, harmless moss snake was slithering past.  Da guards drew deir swords and began circling da snake cautiously.  <br />
<br />
Cries from udder guards inside da city could be heard.  "Snake!  Snake!"  Five more guards  rushed out of da gate to join da first two.  Three more guards came to block da entrance to da city.<br />
<br />
Da seven guards surrounded da snake in a circle so da party couldn't see what was going on.  But swords were flying all over da place, clanging against each udder every few seconds.  Screams of panic and fear were constantly heard from da little group of guards.<br />
<br />
Da moss snake slithered through one of da guard's feet and den hurriedly sped away from da city.  Not noticing at all, da guards continued to hack away.<br />
<br />
One of dem finally said, "It's gone!  We killed it!"  A loud cheer erupted from da guards in da group, da guards at da gate, and several guards up on two battlements who spectated from above.  Patting each udder on da back, da guards marched back to deir posts.<br />
<br />
"Sorry about that" a guard said to da group.  "You may enter now."  Da guards made way for da party and Bash's group walked into da city.<br />
<br />
Lilting quietly said to Medsa, "Wow.  Such fuss over something completely harmless.  Makes you wonder what they'd do if they saw a bat or something."<br />
<br />
A guard caught part of da conversation.  "BAT?!!"  Anudder guard heard da guard.  "BAT!  BAT!"  Soon, all da guards were yelling da warning across da whole entrance.<br />
<br />
Twelve guards stormed out of da gate weapons drawn.  Dey began searching for da dangerous threat to da city.<br />
<br />
Bash's group just sighed and continued on into Freeport.<br />
<br />
"Ok," said Bash turning to da party.  "Us needs to find two tings.  We need to get information on how to get to Halas, and if possible, we need to find more peoples to help us fight Smellybreath.  Let's split up and meet back here in an hour, ok?"<br />
<br />
"Sounds good," said Treehugger.<br />
<br />
"Bah," said Medsa, but willing to do it anyway.<br />
<br />
"Okie dokie!" said an excited Lilting.  And wit dat, da party split up.  <br />
<br />
Lilting raced around dis great big city.  He was not used to everyting being bigger dan him.  He ran around and around, poking his head into several different shops and giggling.  He eventually got tired and found his way into a bar.<br />
<br />
Lilting pulled up a barstool.  Da bartender moved over and said, "What can I get for ya, pint-size?"<br />
<br />
"Ummm.  I'm looking for a courageous fighter to help us kill an evil foe!  I'm also looking for the way to Halas.  Do you know where I can get these things?"<br />
<br />
Hearing what da halfling sitting next to him had just said, a grey-haired man turned to Lilting.  "My boy, I can help you.  I am the greatest dragonslayer that ever lived!"<br />
<br />
Lilting just stared in awe of da man.  He knew he had found someone who could surely help.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
