<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Over da treetops Killdead da demon flew.  Looking downward only to spit da occasional demonic loogie on a poor unsuspecting adventurer's head, he kept his flying steadily northbound.<br />
<br />
On occasion, Killdead would hear da shouts of  some mortals auctioning off deir petty wares.  Da demon smiled evilly for he knew da secret, evil pact dat da gods made when dividing up da land.  Dis pact said dat anyone who shouts lame tings or auctions <b>anyting</b> in Faydark will spend da rest of deir lives in da Plane of Pain.  Dis pact also apply to a place called East Commonlands, but da demon wasn't entirely sure where dat was.<br />
<br />
He finally saw da pass dat lead to Emperor Crush's city.  Flying over it he saw many orc  tents and buildings.  Hundreds of orcs were fighting hundreds of different 'heroes' dat comprised of elves, dwarves, humans and gnomes.  It was just one big chaotic mess.  It made Killdead smile and brought a tear to his eye.  But da demon had more important tings to tink about.  He headed straight for da castle in da middle of da orc town.<br />
<br />
"Whatever you say, your <i>majesty</i>," grumbled a dark elf in a red sportcoat.  He standing along side a particularly stupid looking, cross-eyed orc in a castle tower.  "I am here but to <i>serve</i> you," da dark elf said wit obvious sarcasm and disgust.  <br />
<br />
Da orc, being da stupidest of his race, didn't catch any of da elves hidden messages and just took da words at face value.  "That right!" da orc said.  "Me are Crush!  Me are Emper... Eperom... Eeprom... Me are king!  You is just elf!"<br />
<br />
"Oh, you are so correct, oh <i>great one</i>," da elf said rolling his eyes.  "You're the one who's <i>really in charge here</i>!"<br />
<br />
Just den, a small group of dwarves came running up da castle steps into da tower room.  Dey readied deir weapons and growled at da orc king, ready to attack.  Da orc king just looked stupidly onward.  Da dwarves den began to advance until dey caught sight of da da dark elf dat was standing next to da big orc.  <br />
<br />
Da dark elf turned towards da dwarves and made his eyelids become slits.  Da dwarves' eyes opened so wide dey almost popped out of deir heads.  Dey dropped deir weapons and ran screaming in fear from da tower.<br />
<br />
Da dark elf turned back towards da orc.  "As I was saying, <i>your highness</i>, I think that we need to take your orc forces and GURAMMFF!!"<br />
<br />
"What?  What Gurammff?  It nasty high level?  What?  What is it?"  Da orc not notice da elf was gone.  "What?  Gurammff?  It is a gnome, isn't it?  Crush hate gnomes!  Oooh, Crush hate da little GURAKKK!!"<br />
<br />
A big red hand had reached in from da outside window and yanked da dark elf from da  tower.  Anudder hand reached in and yanked da orc.<br />
<br />
Da demon flew a little bit aways from da castle wit da two beings's heads palmed in each hand.  He set dem down not-so-gently on da ground.<br />
<br />
"Crush want to know why you take Crush from castle!" da orc yelled at da demon, seemingly not afraid.  "Crush crush da crushness out of Crush's crushed crushy crush man!"<br />
<br />
Da dark elf, being slightly more quick-witted dan da orc, saw da demon and recognized who he was.  "Forgive his <i>highness</i>, he is not accustomed to one such as great as you visiting <i>his</i> land." da elf said wit a berry low bow.<br />
<br />
Da orc just screamed obscenities at da demon and danced around in a fit threatening Killdead, occasionally even giving him da orc "finger."  Killdead, also being quick witted realized who really was in charge here.<br />
<br />
"<b>I am looking for a group heading towards the ice country where Halas resides.</b>" da demon said towards da elf in his booming, growl of a voice.  "<b>There is a good chance it is being led by an ogre.  Do you know of such a group?  Tell me now or I will kill you where you stand</b>!"<br />
<br />
Da dark elf searched his memory of recent news.  He remembered someting a dark elf scout had told him.  "I have heard of such a group.  They were in Freeport a little less than five days ago."<br />
<br />
Da orc looked confused at dis news, but den nodded an agry nod at da demon like he knew of dis information all along.<br />
<br />
Da elf continued, "It is rumored they acquired a knight who is leading them to the ice country you spoke of.  Our dark elf underground web...er... <i>Emperor</i> Crush's vast orc empire stretches far across these lands and there is little I... er... He doesn't know."<br />
<br />
Da orc just stared his cross-eyed face at da demon wit pride and dignity.  Da demon wanted to just bite him in half, but he knew dere was probably a reason his dark elf friends kept him alive to be used as a puppet.<br />
<br />
"<b>Good</b>," said da demon, "<b>You have served me well, elf.  You shall be rewarded after your soul departs this plane</b>."  Da demon gave anudder look of disgust to da orc king and den flew straight up fifty feet and den zoomed westward.<br />
<br />
"Crush no like stupid red bird!  Crush want it crushed in crush-like manner!"<br />
<br />
Da dark elf sighed.  "But <i>my lord</i>, the bird is already dead.  You killed it, don't you remember?  You slew it thirty seconds ago!"<br />
<br />
Crush not wanting to admit he didn't remember such a ting, just puffed out his chest wit power and conceit and said, "Of course Crush did!  All peoples fear and tremble before Crush!"<br />
<br />
"Of course they do.  Of course they do."  Da dark elf got an even worse look of disgust on  his face.  Some wandering adventurers came nearby and da elf spun towards dem.  "Boo!"<br />
<br />
Da adventurers screamed and bolted da udder way.  "D'Vinn!" dey shouted!<br />
<br />
Soon, udder people shouting "D'Vinn!" and "D'Vinn's out!" and den mass hysteria ensued.  Elves and humans were tripping over each udder to get to da pass dat lead out of Crushbone.  Dwarves and gnomes were getting smooshed under da weight of all da panicking peoples.<br />
<br />
Da dark elf smiled evilly and quietly said wit dripping sarcasm, "Yes, Crush, people do indeed tremble before you." <br />
<br />
"Of course they do!" said da orc who obviously heard.<br />
<br />
And wit dat, da dark elf and orc walked back towards D'Vinn's... er... Crush's castle.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
