<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>"Ahhh... we're almost there!" said da paladin.  "I remember this place.  See that cave?  That's the entrance to Splitpaw, which is in turn the entrance to Everfrost, which is in turn the entrance to Halas.  Golly, I remember killing three dragons on this very spot!"<br />
<br />
Pyra looked a little confused.  "Dragons?  Here?  I think you may have been mistaken, sir.  The only things near here that resemble a dragon are the harmless little gecko lizards that run around.  I should know, because I've fried more than...er... I've seen 'em around!"<br />
<br />
"Geck Ko?  Never heard of the beasts.  All I know is that three dragons appeared one day and I slew them!"  Da paladin beamed proudly and as he threw his shoulders back his rusted armor squeaked loudly.  "Erm, we should get moving."<br />
<br />
Bash suddenly got a chill.  It sent shivers down to da berry marrow of his bones.  He wasn't sure why.  Maybe it was a warning dat someting bad was gonna happen.  Maybe it was a ghost of a family member dat was nearby.  Or maybe it was da fact dat he was mostly naked.  Us will never know.<br />
<br />
Da group marched on towards Splitpaws entrance in da distance.  Da sun was beaming high overhead and casting it's rays down upon da party in triumph.  It had only been a week since dey left Freeport and dey were finally near deir destination.  Hopefully, some mysteries would finally be answered.  <br />
<br />
Lilting was feeling much better ever since Bash had dunked him in da river to wash away da mud.  He was feeling especially much better since his clothes finally dried.  He was happy dat he was with such good friends.  Maybe he could prove himself on this journey to his halfling brothers and finally be accepted as a druid and not a fool.  He hoped with all his halfling might.<br />
<br />
Treehugger was hoping he wouldn't get killed today.  He looked down at his swords hanging from his belt.  How he longed for da day he would be able to use them with some amount of skill.  He longed to even be a fraction of da famous warrior swordsman and teacher, Da Geistmeister.  He hoped one day to meet the revered man, but nobody has seen him in over 20 years.  Treehugger's thoughts eventually drifted over to Medsa.<br />
<br />
Da brown-haired cleric was walking slightly in front of and to da side of da ranger.  She pretended not to notice Treehugger looking at her.  She also pretended not to care.  She hid her blushing well.<br />
<br />
Pyra was walking behind everyone else.  Not because she was slow, but mostly because she didn't want anyone to see dat she was setting  trees and plants and anyting else ablaze wit some fireball spells as dey passed dem.  She quietly giggled as she set another tree stump on fire.<br />
<br />
"Here we are!" said Yessir as he stopped at da cave's entrance.  "I'd better go ahead and check to make sure no dragons are lurking just inside the cave entrance.  I've found a few there before.  Wait for me, I'll be right back!"<br />
<br />
Da paladin pulled out his rusted sword and wit a battle cry and armor squeaking and grating loudly, he charged into da cave.  Bash couldn't see how a dragon could fit into da tiny, seven foot cave.  He began to wonder if dis paladin really what he said he was.<br />
<br />
Den da thought disappeared just as it came when Bash felt his hammer grow very, very, warm for an instant and den cool down just as fast.  Almost like it was warning him about someting.  Bash didn't want to take any chances.<br />
<br />
"Yessir, wait!" screamed da ogre. "Don't go..."<br />
<br />
It was too late.  Da paladin vanished from sight as he ran deeply into da cave.  Da group looked at Bash and wondered why he would have yelled what he did.<br />
<br />
Den dey found out why.<br />
<br />
A loud <i>CLANG!</i> was heard and Yessir came flying out of da cave backwards wit tremendous force.  He flew horizontally about 30 feet and den slammed into da ground, unconscious.  Da group just stared wit jaws agape and in shock as dey watched da paladin go limp.<br />
<br />
Den dey heard a very low, growling chuckle come from da cave.  Dey turned and saw two bright, white orbs in da cave moving up and down wit da chuckling.  Da group den saw da orbs move closer and dey heard loud <i>THUD</i> followed by anudder.  Bash saw what da orbs were.  Dey were eyes.<br />
<br />
A fifteen foot tall demon, hunched over, pulled himself out of da cave and stood upright in da noon sun in front of da party.  Sunlight glistened off its red scales and black horns.  Da demon waved its hand and a sword appeared in it.  Da blade was black, so black dat light seemed to be absorbed into it and lost forever.<br />
<br />
Da demon smiled a wicked, evil smile dat bared all his long, sharp teeth.  It pointed its sword right at Bash and den laughed.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
