<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Bash no could believe what he saw.  One of his friends just dropped to da ground dead.  He knew dat it would happen again and again if he no did anyting.  He grabbed Medsa and picked her up and ran to where da demon was.<br />
<br />
Yessir made finally made it to da demon.  Out of breath, he took off his bucket-helmet and threw it to da ground.  Da old man's grey hair was sticking out in every direction.  His eyes were filled wit rage.<br />
<br />
"Ok, demonspawn," spat da paladin.  "Let's see you fight me when I'm expecting ye!"<br />
<br />
Da demon turned his attention from da limp ranger to da paladin.  Da demon licked da blood from his hand and den grinned at Yessir.  "<b>Looks like my belly will be rather full tonight</b>!"<br />
<br />
Yessir charged wit rusted sword raised and trash-can shield held high above his head.  But as he ran underneath da demon, he did what nobody, not even da demon expected.  He jumped high into da air and spun in da air to  deliver a roundhouse kick to da demon's face.  He landed on da ground wit sword poised ready to strike.<br />
<br />
Killdead's head twisted to da side wit da blow of da paladin's foot.  He slowly turned back to da paladin wit a look of amazement and puzzlement.<br />
<br />
Yessir grinned.  Den he swung madly at da demon.  Another swordfight bewtween mortal and demon ensued.<br />
<br />
Da demon didn't see da ogre approach.  Bash pointed to where Treehugger lay.  "Heal him," da ogre said to da cleric.<br />
<br />
"I can't!  He's... he's dead!" cried Medsa.<br />
<br />
"Heal him!  Heal him now!  You can do it.  Me know yous can.  Me need him alive for plan to work."<br />
<br />
"I'll.... I'll try."  da cleric said wit a sob and went to da ranger.<br />
<br />
Bash felt da heat from his hammer more intensely.  It kept getting hotter.  He approached da dazed halfling and wizardess.  "Ok yous two... listen up, us not have much time."<br />
<br />
Medsa knelt down next to Treehugger.  She saw da wound da ranger suffered was deep and gaping indeed.  She choked back her tears.  Da rangers eyes stared blankly at da sky above and his hands still clutched tightly to his swords.<br />
<br />
Medsa just wanted to leave dis awful, awful place.  Run away from all dese emotions dat appeared from nowhere.  Fear, hate, mourning, and... love.  She knew she couldn't dough.  Her friends needed her.  Bash needed her.  Treehugger needed her.  She mustered up her courage and placed her hands six inches above da ranger's wound.<br />
<br />
Yessir did his best to block da demon's attacks, but he was nowhere near da fighter dat Treehugger was and he knew it.  "If this thing were only a dragon..." da paladin muttered out of breath.  It was only a matter of time before da demon overtook him.<br />
<br />
White light flared from Medsa's hands.  It grew brighter until encompassed both her and Treehugger.  Her face contorted and strained wit pain and concentration.  Da light grew so bright dat she no could see anyting anymore.  She put all of her energy she had into dis spell.  All of her hope, all of her mind,....and all of her heart.  "Come back to me...... please...."  Den she screamed from da pain da spell demanded of her.<br />
<br />
Da light disappeared.<br />
<br />
Da light distracted da demon for a moment as he looked to see where da source of it was coming from.  It was all Yessir needed.  Da paladin stabbed his sword into da demon's wing and tore downwards, ripping da leathery wing open.<br />
<br />
Da demon roared in pain and anger.  It kicked da paladin square in da chest and sent him flying.<br />
<br />
Medsa collapsed from fatigue.  Da spell had drained her.  Treehugger just lay there, motionless still.  Medsa wailed for her lost friend.  She did not know what else dere was to do.<br />
<br />
Da ranger'ss eyes continued to stare into nothingness.  Until, dat is, dey blinked.  His eyes blinked once more.  He turned his head to da prone cleric.  "Hey.... baby," da ranger rasped.  "Couldn't stand to.... be without me for..... two minutes, huh?"</p>
	
	
	
	
	
