	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Medsa laughed as tears of relief streamed down her face.  She did her best to try and hide her joy, but it didn't work too well.  "Shut up, worm!" she tried to say wit a scowl.  "Bash.... Bash needs you to fight...." da cleric was growing weaker.  She needed to rest badly.  "Can you.... can you fight?"<br />
<br />
Da ranger sat up.  He looked at his torn armor and saw dat a scar was now visible where da demon and ripped him open.  "I think I can.  I believe I owe a certain demon some steel."  And wit dat, da ranger leapt to his feet.<br />
<br />
Medsa smiled and den passed out.<br />
<br />
Da demon stomped up to da paladin on da ground.  It raised it sword to strike at da old man.  It was about to swing until it felt  someting tapping its shoulder.  Killdead turned his head to see what it was.<br />
<br />
"Hiyas," said Bash.  "Remember me?"  Da ogre slammed his hammer into da side of da demon's skull.  Da demon spun about in a 360.  It came to a stop and shook off da daze.  It roared.<br />
<br />
"Yeah yeah, me heard dat before."  Bash stabbed his hammer into da demon's chest and Killdead staggered for a second.  It den raised it's sword in a flash and began swinging at da ogre.<br />
<br />
"Pyra, NOW!" da ogre screamed.  Off to da side, da wizardess began summoning fire from out of nowhere dat collected around her hands.  It accumulated into da largest fireball she ever cast.  She sent it reeling towards da ogre and demon.<br />
<br />
"<b>Foolish ogre</b>," da demon growled.  "<b>Have you learned nothing yet?  Such a spell cannot harm me</b>!"<br />
<br />
"It not for you," said Bash calmly.  "It for me."<br />
<br />
Da fireball slammed into da ogre.  Flames arced all around Bash, but none of it touched him.  Bash's hammer took all da fire in like it was hungry for it.  Flames swirled and swooped into da hammer.  Da demon furrowed his brow in confusion as it looked down at da flashing orange hammer.  Da next ting it saw was da hammer slamming into its torso.<br />
<br />
The sound of a thunderbolt ripped through da air as da hammer struck.  A ring of fire spread outwards and da demon went flying straight back.  Killdead slammed into da rock wall right next to da mouth of da cave.  It fell over in a lump on da ground.  <br />
<br />
Bash grinned.<br />
<br />
Yessir got up and shook his head violently to  regain his senses.  He trotted up next to Bash.  Treehugger arrived seconds later.<br />
<br />
"Is it dead?" da ranger asked.<br />
<br />
"Probably not," said Bash.<br />
<br />
Da ogre was right.  Killdead got onto his feet.  It did not look happy.  But it did look like it had been hurt.<br />
<br />
"Guys, us need to fight it at da same time," said Bash.  "Charge!"<br />
<br />
Da three of dem went at da demon.  Killdead did his best to deflect a blow, but as soon as he blocked one, anudder sword or hammer slammed into his body.  Treehugger jumped into da air, did a flip, slammed his swords into da demons shoulders, and den leapt off da demon's back pulling his swords wit him.<br />
<br />
Killdead was losing, and he knew it.  Da hammer-fire dat slammed into him hurt him more dan he thought any mortal weapon ever could.  But he had a few tricks up his sleeve yet.<br />
<br />
Da demon arced his back and roared. He became surrounded by a red flame.  He seemed stronger.  His wounds seemed to heal, and his tear in his wing sealed up.  Da flames went away and da demon smiled.<br />
<br />
He den attacked wit a ferocity dat dey had never seen before.  Bash expected da demon would not be easy to defeat.<br />
<br />
"Lilting, us need dat teleport now!  It is distracted!  Cast it now!"<br />
<br />
Da halfling was waiting for da ogre to say so.  He began his spell.<br />
<br />
Bash fought as hard as he could.  He knew Treehugger and Yessir were giving it deir best as well.  He just had to keep da demon from disrupting da halfling so Lilting could evacuate dem away from da demon and maybe dey could hide from it until dey could figure out how to destroy it.<br />
<br />
Lilting waved his hands some more.  He knew his teleport spell would take several moments to cast.  Da halfling it was up to him now.  He had an idea.  He spoke da magical words, "Woodland spirits, my voice hear it.  Come down from above, and give me the power to teleport with love!"  <br />
<br />
Da halfling's hands spewed forth blue sparks.  But instead of pointing dem at himself and his friends, he pointed dem at da demon.<br />
<br />
"Lilting!  What is you doing?!" yelled Bash.  "What is you....?" his words were cut short as he watched what happened.<br />
<br />
Da demon looked at da halfling wit puzzlement.  His body became surrounded by da blue sparks.  "<b>Fool!  What do you think you will accomplish?  You cannot get rid of me on this mortal plane!  I can find you from anywhere on this world!  I can....</b>" da demon's voice started to fade.  Da demon started phase out of dis area.<br />
<br />
Da sparks swirled around da demon faster and faster and den da demon and da sparks disappeared all together.<br />
<br />
"Lilting!" said Bash.  "Dat was great!  But he'll back... he said...."<br />
<br />
"Don't worry guys," shouted da halfling.  "Trust me, he's not coming back.  I call that my 'Reverse Port'." Lilting winked.<br />
<br />
----------<br />
<br />
Killdead opened his eyes.   He found it hard to see because of all da bright light around him.  White light seemed to permeate da area all around him.  His eyes started to adjust and he saw dat he was standing on some cotton-like clouds.  His eyes adjusted further and he saw houses all around him made out of da same cloud-like material.<br />
<br />
A gnome in a white robe appeared from one of da buildings and saw da demon.  "Brothers and sisters!" da gnome called out.  "Come!  See!  A new friend!"<br />
<br />
Da demon raised one eyebrow.  He saw hundreds of gnomes, dwarves, and halflings pour out of all da buildings around him.<br />
<br />
"He looks like he needs a hug!" da first gnome said.<br />
<br />
"Yes!  Yes!  Hug!  Hug!" all da udders started to say cheerily around da demon.<br />
<br />
Da demon was suddenly filled wit terror and dread.  He knew where he was.<br />
<br />
One halfling came and hugged Killdead's leg.  Den anudder followed.  Da demon screamed in fright.  He knew where he was indeed.  A place he never hoped to see.  Da Plane of Love.<br />
<br />
More and more little peoples piled onto da demon.  "We love you!  We love you!" da all started chanting wit happiness.<br />
<br />
Da demon was toppled by so many of da little guys piling onto him.  He screamed again.  He began clawing at da ground to try and get away.  It was useless as he became swarmed.<br />
<br />
Killdead screamed in horror one last time before it was muffled.  Da demon disappeared under a huge pile of one big group hug of small peoples.<br />
<br />
--------<br />
<br />
In his castle, Smellybreath's eyes snapped open from meditation.  Da goblin looked at da big black knight standing by his side.<br />
<br />
"There has been a change in plans.  The demon has failed."</p>
	
	
	
	
	
