<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Numbuk</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Ogre Musician<br />
	
	<br /><img src="image.php?s=150f90c73d3c04d5ccf51dbd923c7098&amp;userid=6035&amp;dateline=1034275367" border="0" alt="Avatar" title="Numbuk's Avatar" hspace="4" vspace="4" /><br />
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	Location: Oggok UT, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>"Halt!" shouted a voice from behind Ice.  Da black knight had been continuing his razing of Felwithe for several hours uninterrupted... until now dat is.  Da black knight pulled its giant sword out of his latest high elf kill and turned to face dis nuisance.<br />
<br />
"I am Orclous Calbane!" shouted an elf decked out in fine armor,dat glowed wit magic power, and held two swords dat looked like dey was looted from a powerful dragon's hoarde.  Standing next to him and behind him were several scores of powerful looking peoples of all races and classes.  Wizards, warriors, rangers, magicians, necromancers, monks, everyting.  "Prepare to die, foul fiend!  For all seventy of us are level 62 or higher!  We have destroyed gods and dragons alike in multiple different planes!  You'll soon be nothing but dust in the wind!  Have at you!"<br />
<br />
Da huge group of "high level" peoples charged da black knight holding da glowing blue sword.  Da knight just ****ed its helmeted head in curiosity as da peoples came rushing towards him.<br />
<br />
About thirty seconds later Ice walked away from a berry bloody, destroyed section of town.  In his left hand he held da head of "Orclous Calbane," da idiot elf who thought he and his buddies could kill da Elemental Guardian.  Da knight shook his head and den tossed da elf's noggin behind him as he went deeper into da city to do some more killing and destroying.<br />
<br />
---------<br />
<br />
<br />
Bash began to awaken from a deep, unconscious slumber.  His body hurt too much to move, and he couldn't feel much in terms of his arms and legs.  Da ogre tried to open his eyes, but it only hurt to do so.  He found he was able to squint witout da pain being so bad.<br />
<br />
He saw dat he was lying on his back.  He also noticed dat a single torch was attached to da wall near his head.  It didn't give off a tremendous amount of light, but it was enough to hurt his eyes further.  He saw dat da wall and floor around him was made of rock and ice.  And since da light no hit da ceiling, and since his breathing echoed loudly, he could only guess he was in a huge cavern.  Anyting beyond dat, da light would not penetrate.<br />
<br />
Bash tried to sit up but found he was berry much unable to do so.  He got his head up a couple feet before he felt completely spent of energy and had to plop back down.  He was berry tired and berry sore.  He was able to see dat somone had put some blankets and straw over da ogre to keep him warm while he slept.<br />
<br />
Bash was confused.  He tried to tink of da tings dat happened before he blacked out.  He remembered floating along da raging river.  He remembered da passed out gnome.  He remembered....  he remembered.... he almost remembered someting else when he heard sounds of footsteps.<br />
<br />
Da light from da torch no would let Bash see what was going beyond da length of his make-shift bed.  But he could tell dat da footsteps were entering da same cavern he was in.  Bash's ringing ears were able to distinguish two different patterns of footprints.  One set was light, and da udder... da udder set was...<br />
<br />
"So, the promising ogre has awakened" a berry, berry deep but comforting and somewhat  famliar voice spoke.  "I am glad to see you are not dead."<br />
<br />
Da sound of da lighter footsteps began to walk around his bed as da voice spoke.  "I knew you would come, just as you did.  Just as <i>he</i> did.  I expect there are many questions you must have.  I will do my best to answer what I can."<br />
<br />
"Where is me?" asked Bash in a raspy voice.  It felt like he no used his voice box in ages.<br />
<br />
Da deep voice chuckled, but in a non-threatening or mean way.  "You're deep underground.  Beneath the frozen, icy fields of Permafrost.  Below the barbarian city of Halas."<br />
<br />
"Where..... where is me friends...?"<br />
<br />
"They go to seek the help of the primitives...er... barbarians as you call them, for their help in rescuing you.  It is too bad they do not have the gift, for they would know you are in far safer hands than one could imagine.<br />
<br />
"You have spent your time searching for a certain person, Bash.  You have faced many dangers and acquired powerful allies into finding the one who can guide you along your path.  Your grandfather knew you would find that person.  And now you have.  You have found... me."<br />
<br />
"And..." Bash wheezed, "Who are you?"<br />
<br />
A larger-dan-average gold-tinted skeleton stepped out of da shadows.  It stood next to Bash.  Bash looked at da ting in curiosity.  He wasn't expecting a skeleton to be da ting he had been looking for.<br />
<br />
Bash den heard a louder, heavier set of footsteps come closer to him.  Out of da darkness emerged da biggest, white-est bear Bash had ever seen.  <br />
<br />
Da bear began speaking and Bash recognized da voice as da one he'd just been listening to.<br />
<br />
"I am the oracle."<br />
<br />
Bash, unable to stay awake any longer, let his head fall backwards and den slipped back into a deep rest.<br />
<br />
"Rest now," said da bear.  "All will be revealed in good time."</p>
	
	
	
	
	
