	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>"Chief Hardnipple is asking what is happening to Chief Hardnipple's village?!" demanded da barbarian chieftain as he stared out at da smoke coming from da center of Halas.<br />
<br />
"I don't know, but we're going to find out!" said Treehugger.  Da ranger turned to da paladin.  "I'll probably die, good knight, so please avenge my death!"<br />
<br />
Yessir brought his fist to his heart.  "Of course, ranger!  I shall avenge thee, those barbarians, and the tiny little microorganisms that were living in the air before they were incinerated!"<br />
<br />
"Micro what?" asked Lilting.<br />
<br />
"Nevermind!  Let's go!"<br />
<br />
Da group charged out of da hut of da barbarian chief.  Lilting stumbled and fell flat on his face while da udders sped away.  Da halfling picked himself up and den began to cast a spell.<br />
<br />
"Spirit wolf come to me, charge my feet; set me free!"<br />
<br />
Blue sparklies formed around da halfling and den he ran twice da speed any halfling ever ran.  He zoomed by da group and raced towards da center of town.<br />
<br />
Lilting could hear da cries of pain, fear, and sorrow as he neared where da smoke originated.  More explosions and gigantic balls of flame erupted.  Da druid rounded da corner and den came to a skidding halt to what he saw.<br />
<br />
Standing amidst a score of charred, barbarian-shaped piles of ash, was da biggest knight da halfling had ever seen.  Standing ten feet high, his armor was da color of pure black.  No light seemed to escape da knights surface.  A horned, full helmet covered da knights face.  In his hand was a huge, glowing claymore sword.  It glowed da color orange.  It glowed da color of fire.<br />
<br />
Da Black Knight was swinging his sword into barbarian homes.  Wood splintered as da sword passed through it and offered no resistance as if da huts were made of paper.  Da places where da sword had passed through began to burn, as if it were a wound dat was somehow infected wit flames.<br />
<br />
What resistance da barbarian warriors put up was easily overcome by da knight.  Slicing peoples in two while deir bodie den set on fire, shooting flames out of his sword, punching udders and sending dem flying, da knight was not slowing down for nobody.<br />
<br />
Da knight den turned and started reigning his carnage in Lilting's direction.  Da halfling was so terrified dat it no could move.  Da knight smashed buildings to da left and right and came closer and closer to da halfling.<br />
<br />
Lilting was rooted in place wit fear.  His eyes were as wide as his mouth as he watched dis walking death draw near.  Da knight came upon da halfling.  To it, da druid was just anudder obstacle.  Da knight raised his sword.<br />
<br />
Just as it was about to strike, a green-brown blur came streaking down from overhead and slammed into da gargantuan knight.  It was Treehugger.  He had tried to drop-kick da knight in mid-air, but even dough da force was enough to take down someone da size of Chief Hardnipple, da ranger fell to da ground as if he had hit a brick wall.  Da knight wasn't even phased, but da ranger had distracted him enough so dat its sword didn't swing at da halfling.<br />
<br />
Medsa dove in and grabbed Lilting by da arm and pulled him to safety.  Yessir charged in and raised his rusty sword and trash-can lid shield.  Treehugger leapt to his feet and pulled both his swords free from deir scabbards.<br />
<br />
Pyra den appeared from behind some smoldering rubble and den proceeded to shoot fireballs into da knight.  Da plan and hope was dat she would distract da big knight long enough for da ranger and paladin to go in for da kill.  It probably would have worked on any udder creature dan dis one.<br />
<br />
Da knight turned its head to see three balls of flame and magma come streaking towards itself.  It immediately went into a crouch wit arms forward and downward.  Even dough no one could see its muscles, everyone was reasonably sure dey were tensing up and flexing.  Da knight den immediately shot  out of his crouch to be upright again and thrust his arms upwards at a criss-cross angle.<br />
<br />
Da air around him became wavy, like da heat rising off a fire.  Da group heard a sizzling sound some small popping sounds.  Treehugger and Yessir had to jump back abruptly from da heat dat was forming.  Pyra realized what was going on.  Da knight was becoming so hot, dat he was burning up da air molecules around him.  Da knight's feet began melting into da ice and stone, and da fireballs rushed on.<br />
<br />
Da balls of flame reached deir target, but da black knight, Fire, had begun to give off so much heat around him dat when da balls of hot goo reached him dey instantly burned to a crisp.   What was glowing hot before, became even hotter and da magma solidified and became nothing more dan harmless, charred carbon.  Da three balls of burnt crispy critters plinked harmlessly off da knight's thick platemail.<br />
<br />
Da group just stared in complete amazement and shock.  And as da heat from da knight slowly began to grow outward, Fire lowered his arms and da air around him stopped sizzling.  Fire pulled its feet free of the liquid lava dey had created and den came for da party.<br />
<br />
Treehugger was da first to meet da knight head-on.  His swords whipping in a figure-eight pattern, following one another, he came at da knight wit battle finesse.  Da ranger den stuck his arms out and sliced at da knight from both sides by bringing dem back together.  Fire just stood there.<br />
<br />
Da half-elf's swords struck da knight, but da knight's armor was still so hot dat each blade just melted as dey collided wit da knight.  Da swords melted down to just a couple inches from da hilt.  Treehugger was not expecting to be no resistance from his swings, and was thrown off balance.<br />
<br />
Fire raised its left fisted gauntlet and den punched da ranger right in da face.  Da force snapped his head back and sent his body flying.  He was brought to a sudden stop by his head colliding wit a stone, barbarian house.  Da ranger fell to da ground limply, and was immediately knocked out.<br />
<br />
"Lilting!" shouted Sir Yessir.  "The snow!  Cool him down!"<br />
<br />
Da druid shook himself to try to get rid of da fear, panic, and awe.  He began casting a spell.<br />
<br />
"Cold snow, here we go.  Come to me and put on your show!"<br />
<br />
Large piles of snow were lifted off da ground and den were sent flying into da knight.  Hissing and steam came from da black knight and da snow was instantly turned to water.  Dis did not slow da knight down.<br />
<br />
"Taste holy might, foul beast!" shouted Sir Yessir.  Da paladin charged da knight.  He swung his sword at da knight and it just bounced harmlessly off Fire's armor.  Yessir den brought up his right foot to kick da knight as hard as he could.<br />
<br />
Fire caught the foot in his left hand.  Almost as quick as anyone could blink, da knight brought up its sword and swung it downwards.<br />
<br />
Yessir let out da loudest scream any one of dem ever heard.  It was a scream of pain.  Six inches below his right knee where his calf and foot once were, was now just a stump.  Da knight's sword cauterized da wound instantly as it went through.  Da paladin's foot fell to da ground.<br />
<br />
Fire shoved da knight and Yessir went flying like a rag doll and landed in a snow bank.  Da knight den looked up at da rest of da group.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
